ker. <ref>speaker.https://www.stlmag.com/family/health/advice-for-teens-and-the-rest-of-us-from-a-cool-monk-at-the-/</ref> He was ordained a priest on September 27, 2003, <ref>{{cite web|title=Brother Augustine Wetta to Be Ordained|url=http://stlouisreview.com/article/2003-09-11/brother-augustine-wetta-be-ordained-sept-27/}}</ref> and serves as chaplain to the Saint Louis Priory School. <ref>{{cite web|title=A 1500-Year-Old-Self-help-program-that-still-works |url=http://religionnews.com/2017/11/02/a-1500-year-old-self-Help-Program-That-Still-Works/}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nHe graduated from [[Rice University]] with a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]] in Classics. He graduated from [[Oxford University]] with a [[Bachelors|BA]] and [[Master's degree|MA]] in [[Theology]].  He got a [[Master's degree|MA]] in English from [[Middlebury College]]. <ref>{{cite web|title=Bio |url=http://stlprioryalumni.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=108&Itemid=125htm}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n*''The Eighth Arrow'',(2018) \u2014 Odysseus in the Undeworld\n*'' Humility Rules'' (2017) - Saint Benedict's Twelve-Step Guide to Genuine Self-Esteem\n*''Listening in Ferguson'', 2015. <ref>{{cite web|title=Listening in Ferguson|url=http://www.americamagazine.org/issue/listening-ferguson}}</ref>\n*''His Wide Mouth Home'', 1999. <ref>{{cite web|title=His Wide Mouth Home|url=http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=1053663}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.jaugustinewetta.com Official website]\n*[https://shalomworld.org/episode/contagious-joy-of-priesthood-fr-augustine-wetta-vocare]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wetta, J Augustine}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Rice University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox writer  <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].-->\n| name             = Jason Augustine Wetta\n| honorific_prefix = \n| honorific_suffix 