ipedia:WikiProject_Football/Clubs\n  \u2013 This is Wikipedia, NOT a football gazette.\n  \u2013 Any unconfirmed and unsourced signing/transfer WILL BE reverted at sight. \n  \u2013 Thank You in advance.\n  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\n===Reserve teams===\n{{Main|Tiburones Rojos de Veracruz Reserves and Academy|l1=Veracruz Reserves and Academy}}\n\n;[[Albinegros de Orizaba]]\n:Reserve team that plays in the [[Liga Premier de M\u00e9xico|Liga Premier]] in the third level of the Mexican league system.\n\n==Managers==\n{{col-begin-small}}\n{{col-2}}\n* {{flagicon|Spain}} [[Joaqu\u00edn Urquiaga]] (1947\u201348)\n* {{flagicon|Yugoslavia}} [[Bora Milutinovi\u0107|Velibor \"Bora\" Milutinovi\u0107]] (July 1, 1988\u201388)\n* {{flagicon|Brazil}} [[Eduardo Antunes Coimbra|Edu Antunes]] (1991)\n* {{flagicon|Chile}} [[Carlos Reinoso]] (1992\u201394)\n* {{flagicon|Peru}} [[Miguel Company]] (July 1, 1993\u2013Dec 31, 1993)\n* {{flagicon|Mexico}} [[Tom\u00e1s Boy]] (Sept 23, 1995\u2013June 30, 1996)\n* {{flagicon|Argentina}} [[Luis Manuel Blanco]] (July 1, 1997 \u2013 June 30, 1998)\n* {{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[H\u00e9ctor Hugo Eugui]] (1999)\n* {{flagicon|Bolivia}} [[Carlos Trucco]] (2000)\n* {{flagicon|Argentina}} [[Pablo Centrone]] (2001)\n* {{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[Hugo Fern\u00e1ndez]] (2002)\n* {{flagicon|Israel}} [[Daniel Brailovsky]] (Sept 27, 2002\u2013Dec 31, 2002)\n* {{flagicon|Mexico}} [[Daniel Guzm\u00e1n]] (Jan 1, 2003\u2013March 14, 2004)\n* {{flagicon|Mexico}} [[Tom\u00e1s Boy]] (March 20, 2004 \u2013 June 30, 2004)\n* {{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[Wilson Graniolatti]] (July 1, 2004\u2013Feb 28, 2005)\n* {{flagicon|Mexico}} [[V\u00edctor Manuel Vucetich]] (March 4, 2005 \u2013 June 30, 2005)\n* {{flagicon|Mexico}} [[Alfredo Tena]] (Jan 1, 2006\u2013Feb 14, 2006)\n* {{flagicon|Mexico}} [[V\u00edctor Manuel Vucetich]] (March 3, 2006\u2013Sept 3, 2006)\n* {{flagicon|Argentina}} [[Pedro Monz\u00f3n]] (Sept 7, 2